<subSubSection id="C30F0386B136FF93FF6DFC9FFDA7FB0D" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB136FF93FF6DFC9FFDA7FB0D" blockId="3.[174,1233,890,1813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
D i a g n o s i s. Usually large, robust species; wing 7–21 (usually 9–19) mm long, largely yellow or grey, usually with apex dark grey or brown; scutellum with 3–6 pairs of scutellar setae, except in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FE56FC5EFDDDFC6C" authorityName="Korneyev" authorityYear="2006" box="[472,603,954,980]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="echinata">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FE56FC5EFDDDFC6C" box="[472,603,954,980]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">E. echinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Korneyev, 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FD68FC5EFBA6FC6D" authority="(Brunetti)" baseAuthorityName="Brunetti" box="[742,1056,954,981]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melancholica">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FD68FC5EFC19FC6C" box="[742,927,954,980]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">E. melancholica</emphasis>
(Brunetti)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FBA3FC5EFEBEFC4D" authority="(Enderlein)" baseAuthorityName="Enderlein" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Peltodasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vespiformis">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FBA3FC5EFB56FC6C" box="[1069,1232,954,980]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">E. vespiformis</emphasis>
(Enderlein)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FEF0FC3EFDC3FC4D" authority="(Bigot)" baseAuthorityName="Bigot" box="[382,581,986,1013]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagae">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FEF0FC3EFE61FC4C" box="[382,487,987,1012]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">E. wagae</emphasis>
(Bigot)
</taxonomicName>
with 2 pairs of setae; fore trochanter of female often with short spiny (or hook-like) setulae. Oviscape uniformly sclerotized, with 2 robust wide ventral hooks anterior of apex and short desclerotized area between them. Male with epandrium moderately elongate in profile, with lateral surstylus often somewhat pointed posteroventrally, densely covered with thick but short setulae; phallus glans with asymmetrical sclerites of acrophallus (conspicuously developed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C152B8EB136FF93FC3EFB9EFB93FB2C" box="[944,1045,1147,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Pyrgotidae" genus="Eupyrgota" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wagae">
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FC3EFB9EFB93FB2C" box="[944,1045,1147,1172]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">E. wagae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF842DFCB136FF93FBD6FB9FFF6CFB0C" author="Korneyev, V. A." pageId="3" pageNumber="114" pagination="19 - 46" refId="ref10584" refString="Korneyev, V. A. Genera of Palaearctic Pyrgotidae (Diptera, Acalyptrata), with nomenclatural notes and a key // Vestnik zoologii. - 2004. - 38, N 1. - P. 19 - 46." type="journal article" year="2004">Korneyev, 2004</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 16, 
<emphasis id="B9618C1FB136FF93FEC6FB7FFEF7FB0C" box="[328,369,1178,1204]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">1, 4</emphasis>
; 2006 a: 
<figureCitation id="132E4C88B136FF93FE56FB7FFD92FB0D" box="[472,532,1178,1205]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="12.[166,199,1666,1688]" captionTargetBox="[220,1195,215,1565]" captionTargetId="figure-8@12.[188,1210,206,1590]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="Fig. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., holotype ♀ (NMKE): 1 — habitus, left; 2–5 — head (2 — anterior left; 3 — anterior; 4 — left; 5 — dorsal); 6 — fore femur, posterior view; 7 — mid femur, anterior; 8 — wing; 9 — abdomen, ventral. Рис. 6. Eupyrgota nyambene, sp. n., голотип ♀ (NMKE): 1 — общий вид, слева; 2–5 — голова (2 — спереди слева;3 — спереди; 4 — слева;5 — дорсально); 6 — переднее бедро,вид сзади;7 — среднее бедро, спереди; 8 — крыло; 9 — брюшко, вентрально." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6403943" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6403943/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30F0386B136FF93FF6DFB5FFB57F8AD" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA500DB136FF93FF6DFB5FFD88FB4C" blockId="3.[174,1233,890,1813]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">S p e c i e s i n c l u d e d. Twenty-five nominal species correspond to the diagnosis of the subgenus and are placed here:</paragraph>
